Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.87,0:00:08.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When someone leaves behind a will,\Ncivil law specifies a descendant's portion...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.97,0:00:17.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A minimum share of their inheritance which is reserved for\Nthe deceased's heirs, so they are not overly disadvantaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.12,0:00:23.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So long as there's no legal issue\Nsurrounding that inheritance, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.28,0:00:41.11,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Only the light of deductions can tear apart\Nthe pitch-black shadows and bottomless darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.11,0:00:45.11,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Difficult circumstances surround an inheritance battle,\Nand wine concealing a dangerous motive!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.11,0:00:46.70,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.70,0:00:48.67,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.67,0:00:51.34,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.79,0:02:29.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0004,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.15,0:02:31.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0004,,Why were we invited, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.73,0:02:32.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0004,,How should I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.53,0:02:33.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0004,,You don't really care?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.90,0:02:35.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0004,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.32,0:02:40.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0004,,Kotaro Ichikawa may be president of Ichikawa Industries now,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.94,0:02:43.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he's also a deceitful jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.75,0:02:45.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt he has honest work for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.99,0:02:47.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't you say no?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.39,0:02:51.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Grownups have grownup circumstances to take care of!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.61,0:02:53.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yeah, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.50,0:02:56.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He hasn't had any work at all for a long time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.14,0:03:04.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a party going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.51,0:03:09.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The president has a family meeting every year on his birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.60,0:03:14.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} is here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.31,0:03:15.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.10,0:03:20.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ichikawa, the head of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.45,0:03:22.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.29,0:03:27.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just so you know, I haven't decided to help you just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.50,0:03:28.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Imamura.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.49,0:03:30.62,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshiaki Imamura (55)\NIchikawa family butler
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.25,0:03:35.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,100,000 yen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.71,0:03:39.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You must take the great Kogoro Mouri for a cheap joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.28,0:03:43.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.85,0:03:44.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.90,0:03:46.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't 100,000 yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.50,0:03:48.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.14,0:03:51.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One, ten, hundred, thousand,\Nten thousand, hundred thousand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.90,0:03:54.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A million yen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.98,0:03:58.73,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Kotaro Ichikawa (65)\NPresident of Ichikawa Industries
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.34,0:03:58.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've prepared another million yen for you if your job is successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.97,0:04:03.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.64,0:04:04.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.56,0:04:10.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My two daughters will be in attendance at today's family meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.04,0:04:16.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to watch what they do and what they try to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.67,0:04:20.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, should I leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.65,0:04:24.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's fine. You can explain my condition to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.82,0:04:26.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.43,0:04:30.27,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Hitoshi Okano (30)\NKotaro's physician
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.09,0:04:30.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he continues to push himself, there's no guarantee he'll live.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.73,0:04:36.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm thinking of retiring now,\Nbut I need to decide on a successor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.08,0:04:39.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be one of your daughters, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.56,0:04:42.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not necessarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.25,0:04:45.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of sharing my fortune with uncouth vultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.70,0:04:47.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,which may include my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.99,0:04:53.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, inheritances are subject to legally-secured portions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.10,0:04:56.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your children would still get\Na percent of it, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.26,0:05:02.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But not if there's an issue with who it's going to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.41,0:05:04.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Issue?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.58,0:05:11.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's going to happen.\NSomething. I can feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.50,0:05:13.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.72,0:05:17.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've told everyone you're a friend,\Nand that you're with your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.64,0:05:20.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful not to be found out as you do your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.13,0:05:31.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.70,0:05:37.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}. Over there is Kazue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, the eldest daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.48,0:05:40.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She currently manages an art gallery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.98,0:05:45.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Imamura. Who might this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.20,0:05:49.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this is Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, a friend of your father's.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:50.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.31,0:05:52.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Father's friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.01,0:05:57.06,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazue Ichikawa (30)\NEldest daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.93,0:05:57.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it a bother, being forced\Nto attend a gathering like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.43,0:06:00.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not at all! I came with my family...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.40,0:06:03.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...and we're having a great time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.00,0:06:04.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.17,0:06:07.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think you'd actually come.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.47,0:06:10.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I would attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.95,0:06:13.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the next in line in the Ichikawa family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.95,0:06:18.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder. I somehow doubt Father would give everything to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.91,0:06:18.46,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizue Ichikawa (27)\NSecond daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.37,0:06:23.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}did{\i0} act selfishly and leave home after you argued with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.49,0:06:25.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who're you to talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.00,0:06:29.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You got married right away because you were sick of seeing his face!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.26,0:06:34.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, I hear your art gallery is being sued
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.47,0:06:36.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,for selling forgeries or something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.43,0:06:38.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.87,0:06:41.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}One is as bad as the other...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.00,0:06:59.96,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Cave\N(wine storeroom)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.72,0:07:01.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's Kazue{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.12,0:07:11.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A syringe! What is she planning to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.68,0:07:16.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's in it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.40,0:07:21.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.19,0:07:24.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}C-Chloroform...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.50,0:07:30.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where could Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} have gone off to?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.25,0:07:38.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thank you for gathering here on my birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.85,0:07:42.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I intend to give up my position as company president very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.15,0:07:44.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, I'm retiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.44,0:07:50.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, I've decided to sell all my stock and ownership rights
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.62,0:07:54.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to Nichiuri Industries.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.45,0:07:56.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- What?!\N- Come again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.53,0:08:00.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sir! What happens to us, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.62,0:08:03.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to stay with the company,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.25,0:08:06.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll need to prove your worth to the new administration.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.82,0:08:08.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.74,0:08:11.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What'll you do with the money you make from selling the company?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.49,0:08:15.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How I use it is up to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.17,0:08:18.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of giving any of you a single yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.45,0:08:19.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even my daughters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.56,0:08:29.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Damn, I let my guard down! I gotta hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.70,0:08:33.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It was probably poison she put in the wine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.95,0:08:35.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}How does she plan to use it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.77,0:08:41.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't object to your decision, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.12,0:08:43.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor will I.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.04,0:08:48.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought out a '57 wine to celebrate this new chapter in your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.08,0:08:53.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's worth even more for a wine aficionado like yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.66,0:08:59.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd feel bad for the wine if regular know-nothings like us drank it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.10,0:09:01.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.07,0:09:06.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she's more considerate than I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.40,0:09:09.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I haven't seen Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.69,0:09:16.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.69,0:09:17.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.13,0:09:19.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.75,0:09:27.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Success!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.00,0:09:30.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.45,0:09:44.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.37,0:09:45.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.52,0:09:47.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to Ichikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.05,0:09:48.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He suddenly collapsed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.70,0:09:54.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,President!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.48,0:09:59.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.25,0:10:08.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Father!\N- Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:10.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.68,0:10:15.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an unnatural death for now.\NA police examiner is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.80,0:10:26.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, he collapsed immediately\Nafter drinking the wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.54,0:10:27.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.68,0:10:29.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.55,0:10:34.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He did have a weak heart, but one drink wouldn't have killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.75,0:10:36.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was poison in the wine!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.53,0:10:40.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come again?! Are you suggesting I poisoned it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.49,0:10:43.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the only possibility!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.06,0:10:44.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're horrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.23,0:10:46.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a basis for your claim?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.52,0:10:50.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Okano knows about our father's condition!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.20,0:10:54.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that he had a weak heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.13,0:10:56.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but something so soon and sudden is out of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.21,0:10:58.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.00,0:10:59.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still saying it was me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.65,0:11:04.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now! I'm sorry to ask,\Nbut may we inspect your belongings?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.88,0:11:17.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Okano. Can you tell what's in this vial?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.30,0:11:21.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to be a muscle relaxant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.31,0:11:25.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What would happen if this was given to Mr. Ichikawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.80,0:11:29.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's very dangerous even for healthy individuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.62,0:11:32.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Given that he had a serious heart illness...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.82,0:11:40.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's no question she was the one who poisoned the wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:44.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But just who attacked me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.39,0:11:58.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea as to Kazue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.25,0:12:02.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Her art gallery {\i1}was{\i0} in quite a lot of debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.06,0:12:03.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she was after the inheritance?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.89,0:12:08.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He declared he wouldn't even leave his own daughters a single yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.85,0:12:10.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.71,0:12:14.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd still get our legally-secured portions,\Nno matter what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.10,0:12:16.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if he said nothing,\Nwe'd still get a percentage of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.65,0:12:19.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Did the younger sister attack me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.51,0:12:22.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If she knew about her sister's plan
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.10,0:12:25.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and locked me up to keep me\Nfrom getting in her way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.00,0:12:31.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If the older sister was found guilty,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.23,0:12:33.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the huge inheritance would be all hers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.11,0:12:40.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A single key not on his keychain?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.66,0:12:43.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.95,0:12:45.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What does this key go to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.83,0:12:48.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I think it might be the basement key.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.35,0:12:53.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How odd. He almost never went into the basement...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.46,0:12:57.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.79,0:13:01.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Was it the victim, Ichikawa{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, who threw me into the basement?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.10,0:13:08.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If so, that means he knew the wine was poisoned when he drank it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.23,0:13:09.75,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.22,0:13:26.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A video camera lens!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.28,0:13:29.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The cord goes into the ceiling!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.25,0:13:48.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Was this to record the person who killed him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.79,0:14:18.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This smell... Ichikawa{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} didn't drink the wine after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.32,0:14:24.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He knew the eldest daughter, Kazue{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, had tampered with the wine,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.29,0:14:26.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so he dumped it into this flowerpot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.22,0:14:30.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Then he pretended to drink it and writhe in pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.73,0:14:33.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...to see how both daughters reacted!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.70,0:14:39.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But there's no doubt that he really was poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.05,0:14:42.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I don't get it! How did he ingest the poison?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.06,0:14:47.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Damn kid, scampering around everywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.33,0:14:55.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Maybe they gave him poison in a capsule or something, not wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.60,0:15:00.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No, the time doesn't add up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.34,0:15:02.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.47,0:15:05.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No one could've given him the poison in front of everyone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.62,0:15:08.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Given?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.50,0:15:14.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Only that person could've done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.31,0:15:20.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You damn kid, sneaking into a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.21,0:15:22.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What the?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.31,0:15:31.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.71,0:15:35.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a pathetic personal physician.\NI couldn't save him...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.97,0:15:39.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that! It's not your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.45,0:15:41.98,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm sorry to keep you all waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.61,0:15:46.20,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I've finally figured out the truth behind this incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.20,0:15:48.83,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}so please gather in the business room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.77,0:15:56.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by "the truth," Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.59,0:16:02.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, I have no doubt that Kazue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} poisoned the wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.88,0:16:08.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Ichikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} never drank it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.24,0:16:10.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a sip.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.15,0:16:11.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.96,0:16:16.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He pretended to drink, but dumped it in the flowerpot by the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.47,0:16:18.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it was his heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.53,0:16:24.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. He died of a poison-induced heart attack. I'm certain of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.52,0:16:29.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of nonsense is this?!\NMy sister obviously killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.60,0:16:33.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he just couldn't accept death normally,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.56,0:16:36.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,even though he trusted you two\Nuntil the very last moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.27,0:16:39.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But didn't he hire you to investigate because he didn't trust them?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.81,0:16:44.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted to trust them. So he tested them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.77,0:16:47.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran. Play the video tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.56,0:16:54.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Is this it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.10,0:16:55.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:58.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This was all set up by Ichikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.48,0:17:02.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably planned to pretend\Nto collapse from his heart illness
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.41,0:17:09.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then check later on the tape\Nto see how both daughters reacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.90,0:17:12.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the plan changed somewhat
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.41,0:17:17.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when he learned Kazue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was planning to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.40,0:17:18.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.50,0:17:24.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's when he decided to pretend to drink the poisoned wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.56,0:17:29.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, hold on. Wasn't it poison that caused his death?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.17,0:17:31.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That, we can be certain of.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.83,0:17:35.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it wasn't added to his wine or food.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.64,0:17:38.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was given to him with a more direct method.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.89,0:17:44.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on now. I'm not sure anyone had enough time to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.86,0:17:46.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Everyone was watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.95,0:17:54.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The killer openly gave him the poison while everyone watched.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.00,0:17:56.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran. Pause the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.04,0:17:59.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.50,0:18:04.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.45,0:18:05.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Okano.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.85,0:18:11.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You{\i0} could've given him a shot of poison instead of a heart stimulant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.97,0:18:17.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You knew of Ichikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s plan, did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.16,0:18:18.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.44,0:18:23.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he would've required his doctor's help to put on the act.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.78,0:18:29.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, you would've realized he was faking right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:36.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} confided his plan to you alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.99,0:18:39.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what that plan was,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.07,0:18:45.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but you decided to use it\Nas a chance to murder him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.64,0:18:50.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone knew he had a weak heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:55.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So no one would doubt his personal physician's diagnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.40,0:19:00.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?! He has nothing to do\Nwith the inheritance, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.20,0:19:04.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The most likely possibility is revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.25,0:19:06.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As his personal doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.87,0:19:12.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there was no need to dirty your own hands to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.64,0:19:16.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you had told him his condition wasn't serious, given how he was,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.68,0:19:23.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he would've kept pushing himself, hastening his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.63,0:19:27.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact you instead took direct action...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.51,0:19:29.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I despised him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.88,0:19:32.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To that extent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.54,0:19:39.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The president—no, Kotaro Ichikawa—killed my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.25,0:19:47.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichikawa and my father were partners when the business started.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.95,0:19:50.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It happened 30 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.97,0:19:55.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The venture business they started together was a great success.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.28,0:19:59.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then he backstabbed my father and kicked him out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.65,0:20:01.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,without even a yen to his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.13,0:20:05.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Family life was miserable after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.95,0:20:09.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He would always utter complaints\Nto me, just a little kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.59,0:20:14.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, my mother passed away\Nbefore I entered middle school,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.50,0:20:19.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and my father hastened his own death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.80,0:20:25.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, after I became a doctor, this man appeared before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.82,0:20:32.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He never realized who I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.90,0:20:39.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But when he told me about his plan to test his daughters' loyalty,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.50,0:20:41.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I suddenly made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.58,0:20:47.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A horrible backstabber like him,\Ntesting the loyalty of others...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.29,0:20:49.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had to make him pay...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.57,0:20:53.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had to make him pay!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.19,0:22:32.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to be busy now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.65,0:22:35.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to organize the things Father left me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.32,0:22:36.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.53,0:22:39.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam! About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.95,0:22:44.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father said in his will that if something should happen to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.33,0:22:46.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,everything should be donated away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.95,0:22:49.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid! I won't allow any such thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.97,0:22:54.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he did have the will written in the presence of an attorney...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.12,0:22:58.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. There's something called a "legally-secured portion".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.23,0:23:00.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I insist on receiving what I deserve!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.94,0:23:01.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.94,0:23:03.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.41,0:23:08.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you disposed of your father's stock certificates on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.62,0:23:14.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told the board of directors\Nis charging you with embezzlement.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.25,0:23:19.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way! It's not true! It's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.54,0:23:22.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, Ichikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s daughters
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.69,0:23:26.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,don't even get one yen of his inheritance...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.08,0:23:29.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! What's gonna happen to this house?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.53,0:23:32.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean? It's going to be donated to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.24,0:23:35.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what happens to my pay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.69,0:23:37.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You got a million yen already!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.54,0:23:39.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the other million?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.14,0:23:40.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just forget about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.15,0:23:42.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
